06/07/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Mircea Geoana, the leader of Romania's main opposition Social Democratic Party (PSD), said on Saturday (July 5th) that his party would shoot for 40% of the parliament's seats in the elections this autumn.
Geoana vowed to increase female participation in the legislative and executive structures.
He also said the PSD would propose a new law to clean up party financing.(Mediafax, Rador - 05/07/08)
